assistant:
Write a basic for loop like this:
```
for i = 1 to array.Lastrow do
    arr[i].PaymentReceived = TRUE;
endfor;
```

Use the 'downto' keyword in a for loop like this:
```
for i = 10 downto 1 do
    message 'Countdown: ' || char(i);
endfor;
```

Break out of a for loop using 'endloop' like this:
```
for i = 1 to arr.Lastrow do
    if arr[i].Name = '' then
        endloop;
    endif;
    // Process non-empty names
endfor;
```

Use labels with nested for loops like this:
```
outer: for i = 1 to arr1.Lastrow do
    inner: for j = 1 to arr2.Lastrow do
        if condition then
            endloop outer;
        endif;
    endfor;
endfor;
```

Use the 'continue' statement in a for loop like this:
```
for i = 1 to arr.Lastrow do
    if arr[i].Skip = TRUE then
        continue;
    endif;
    // Process non-skipped items
endfor;
```
